# Housing Price Prediction using Linear Regression

# Project Overview
This project implements Linear Regression to predict housing prices based on various features such as area, number of bedrooms, bathrooms, and other amenities.
The model is built using Python, Pandas, Scikit-learn, and Matplotlib and follows a complete machine learning workflow from data preprocessing to evaluation.

# Objective
* To understand and implement Linear Regression
* To predict house prices based on input features
* To evaluate model performance using standard metrics

# Technologies Used
* Python
* Pandas
* NumPy
* Matplotlib
* Seaborn
* Scikit-learn

# Dataset
* Dataset used: Housing Price Prediction Dataset
* Source: Kaggle
* File: https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/harishkumardatalab/housing-price-prediction

# Steps Performed
# 1. Data Loading
* Uploaded dataset using Google Colab
* Loaded using Pandas

# 2. Data Preprocessing
* Checked for missing values
* Converted categorical variables using One-Hot Encoding
* Prepared dataset for model training

# 3. Feature Selection
* Independent variables (X): All features except price
* Dependent variable (y): Price

# 4. Train-Test Split
* Split dataset into:
  * 80% Training data
  * 20% Testing data

# 5. Model Building
* Used LinearRegression() from Scikit-learn
* Trained model on training data

# 6. Prediction
* Predicted house prices using test data

# Results
* The model successfully predicts house prices based on input features
* Visualization shows relationship between actual and predicted values

# Visualization
* Scatter plot of Actual vs Predicted Prices
* Correlation heatmap for feature relationships

